        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/6d09b81e32b0d4bf/text/000000293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/6d09b81e32b0d4bf/text/000000293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-6d09b81e32b0d4bf-0fdc9a twpub-6d09b81e32b0d4bf-c3c16f twpub-6d09b81e32b0d4bf-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/6d09b81e32b0d4bf/text/000000254\"><span class=\"label\">[O]</span></$link> Thus was I sacrificed to the envy and resentment of this woman for knowing that the lady whom she had succeeded in my master's good graces designed to take me into her service; which, had I once got on shore, she would not have been able to prevent. She felt her pride alarmed at the superiority of her rival in being attended by a black servant: it was not less to prevent this than to be revenged on me, that she caused the captain to treat me thus cruelly.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
